- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as discourse unit segmentation and connective detection.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper describes the use of machine learning techniques to build an ensemble of classifiers for the task.
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of model stacking, which is a technique used in machine learning to improve model performance.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with the segmentation of discourse units, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks such as summarization and question answering.
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with any audio or speech-related tasks.
